01:03:31.240 --> 01:03:33.039
AUDIENCE: Is there
a more direct way

01:03:33.039 --> 01:03:36.641
to think about this for maybe
the example of a magnetic trap,

01:03:36.641 --> 01:03:43.024
the mechanism by which this
momentum is transferred?

01:03:43.024 --> 01:03:45.479
Or absorbed.

01:03:45.479 --> 01:03:46.590
PROFESSOR: OK.

01:03:46.590 --> 01:03:48.530
Magnetic traps for
neutral particles

01:03:48.530 --> 01:03:49.660
are usually not in
the Lamb-Dicke regime,

01:03:49.660 --> 01:03:51.285
so you have to be a
little bit careful.

01:03:58.880 --> 01:04:00.790
But the explanation
would be the same.

01:04:00.790 --> 01:04:05.840
The magnetic fields
are like tight springs

01:04:05.840 --> 01:04:10.050
which connect the neutral
atom to your coins.

01:04:10.050 --> 01:04:12.810
And therefore, you
should just think

01:04:12.810 --> 01:04:16.430
about the magnetic trap
in a mechanical model.

01:04:16.430 --> 01:04:19.430
Your neutral atom is connected
to your coils with strings.

01:04:19.430 --> 01:04:24.670
And if you now hit the
atom with a photon,

01:04:24.670 --> 01:04:28.200
because of the quantization
of the discreteness

01:04:28.200 --> 01:04:31.540
of this specturm, the
photon, in most cases,

01:04:31.540 --> 01:04:34.240
does not have enough
recoil to create

01:04:34.240 --> 01:04:38.445
a mechanical oscillation
of your particle.

01:04:38.445 --> 01:04:41.010
The momentum goes
through the sphinx

01:04:41.010 --> 01:04:42.660
to the support structure.

01:04:42.660 --> 01:04:45.870
But occasionally,
with a probability

01:04:45.870 --> 01:04:48.410
which is a modulation
index squared,

01:04:48.410 --> 01:04:50.910
you will actually
promote the particle

01:04:50.910 --> 01:04:53.410
to the first state
of harmonic motion.

01:04:53.410 --> 01:04:55.680
And then the atom has
acquired some kinetic energy.

01:04:55.680 --> 01:04:57.830
But this probability
can be made as small

01:04:57.830 --> 01:05:01.266
as you want by going to a
smaller and smaller modulation

01:05:01.266 --> 01:05:03.790
index.

01:05:03.790 --> 01:05:05.574
That's the way how I
would think about it.

