01:07:15.230 --> 01:07:19.110
Let me maybe summarize
in words what we learned.

01:07:19.110 --> 01:07:21.500
So what we learned
from this discussion

01:07:21.500 --> 01:07:25.980
is that what matters for
line broadening and obtaining

01:07:25.980 --> 01:07:29.130
spectroscopic information
is the accumulated phase,

01:07:29.130 --> 01:07:32.715
the phase which the
atom accumulates.

01:07:32.715 --> 01:07:35.250
And if different
atoms in the ensemble

01:07:35.250 --> 01:07:40.330
accumulate a phase which
is different by 2 pi,

01:07:40.330 --> 01:07:43.060
at that moment, we
have reached what

01:07:43.060 --> 01:07:47.450
we call the coherence time
of the correlation function.

01:07:47.450 --> 01:07:51.270
And the inverse of this
time is a line broadening.

01:07:51.270 --> 01:07:54.850
But now we also discussed the
case of tight confinement.

01:07:54.850 --> 01:07:58.320
The atom can be in
very, very rapid motion.

01:07:58.320 --> 01:08:01.760
And the phi dot,
the change of phase

01:08:01.760 --> 01:08:04.810
can be very rapid due to
the instantaneous velocity.

01:08:04.810 --> 01:08:07.520
But if the atom turns
around because it's

01:08:07.520 --> 01:08:11.060
in a singulatory motion,
positive and negative Doppler

01:08:11.060 --> 01:08:15.105
shifts completely
cancel, because you never

01:08:15.105 --> 01:08:20.420
allow the atom, in this periodic
motion, to acquire a net phase.

01:08:20.420 --> 01:08:26.510
And therefore, the motional
broadening is absent.

01:08:26.510 --> 01:08:28.950
So one way to think
about this carrier

01:08:28.950 --> 01:08:32.765
is that the atom rapidly
oscillates through plus kv

01:08:32.765 --> 01:08:35.240
and minus kv Doppler shifts.

01:08:35.240 --> 01:08:38.140
And the two cancel.

01:08:38.140 --> 01:08:40.248
So this is the reason for that.

