01:11:56.757 --> 01:11:59.980
go from one count state
with an off-resonant laser

01:11:59.980 --> 01:12:01.640
to another ground
state, [INAUDIBLE]

01:12:01.640 --> 01:12:03.740
will be two photon transitions.

01:12:03.740 --> 01:12:07.980
But those two photons, since
there's no intermediate state,

01:12:07.980 --> 01:12:11.287
can be regarded as, click-click,
you absorb two photons.

01:12:11.287 --> 01:12:12.870
And in some picture--
that's a message

01:12:12.870 --> 01:12:16.810
I will give you next week-- the
equivalent to a single photon.

01:12:16.810 --> 01:12:20.190
So now you have a
two-photon transition,

01:12:20.190 --> 01:12:23.230
which transfers
recall to the atom.

01:12:23.230 --> 01:12:25.792
So the effective wavelengths
of the two-photon transition

01:12:25.792 --> 01:12:29.175
is because you have
twice the photon energy.

01:12:29.175 --> 01:12:31.680
You have two photons involved
which both have a recoil.

01:12:31.680 --> 01:12:36.440
So the effective k vector is two
times the k vector of an atom.

01:12:36.440 --> 01:12:40.070
But the spontaneous line
width is close to 0,

01:12:40.070 --> 01:12:42.420
literally 0, because you
have a Raman transition

01:12:42.420 --> 01:12:46.260
between two common states.

01:12:46.260 --> 01:12:50.130
If you do Raman sideband
cooling of neutral atoms,

01:12:50.130 --> 01:12:51.790
then you reach the
Lamb-Dicke limit,

01:12:51.790 --> 01:12:55.600
you reach the limit
of strong confinement.

01:12:55.600 --> 01:12:57.535
But you need a better
[INAUDIBLE] transition.

01:12:57.535 --> 01:12:59.562
And there are, of
course, some atoms

01:12:59.562 --> 01:13:01.540
which have a very
narrow clock transition.

01:13:01.540 --> 01:13:04.660
But for many, many atoms which
have hyperfine structure,

01:13:04.660 --> 01:13:06.749
you can resolve to
Raman transition.

01:13:10.751 --> 01:13:11.250
OK.

01:13:15.460 --> 01:13:20.104
Let's now talk about
Dicke narrowing.

01:13:23.820 --> 01:13:28.640
So we have a situation that
we have an atom in buffer gas.

01:13:28.640 --> 01:13:33.579
And in most situations, when
you put an atom into buffer gas,

01:13:33.579 --> 01:13:35.495
you get what is called
collisional broadening.

01:13:38.170 --> 01:13:41.500
I will talk about collisional
broadening on Friday.

01:13:41.500 --> 01:13:43.780
Just a reminder, we have
class on Friday but not

01:13:43.780 --> 01:13:44.831
on the following Monday.

01:13:44.831 --> 01:13:47.080
So on Friday, we'll talk
about collisional broadening.

01:13:47.080 --> 01:13:49.406
And I will discuss, for
instance, the model-- an atom

01:13:49.406 --> 01:13:53.624
in the excited state, when it
collides, it gets de-excited.

01:13:53.624 --> 01:13:55.332
And then you have
pretty much a situation

01:13:55.332 --> 01:14:00.150
where you have, in effect,
a shortened lifetime

01:14:00.150 --> 01:14:01.659
of the excited state.

01:14:01.659 --> 01:14:03.200
And what you get is
a Lorentian which

01:14:03.200 --> 01:14:07.766
is broader, which has a width
not of the natural line width,

01:14:07.766 --> 01:14:10.310
but a width which
is [INAUDIBLE].

01:14:10.310 --> 01:14:12.510
But there are
situations-- and that's

01:14:12.510 --> 01:14:15.060
what I want to discuss
here-- that we have

01:14:15.060 --> 01:14:18.630
atoms in a more
benign buffer gas.

01:14:27.110 --> 01:14:30.010
Where we can assume that
this is actually fulfilled,

01:14:30.010 --> 01:14:33.635
that collisions do not change.

01:14:37.310 --> 01:14:40.390
Well, they're not de-exciting
the excited state.

01:14:40.390 --> 01:14:42.905
But they're not even
changing the coherence

01:14:42.905 --> 01:14:45.280
between counter-excited state.

01:14:45.280 --> 01:14:47.720
So the phase evolution,
the internal state,

01:14:47.720 --> 01:14:51.174
grounded excited
state just-- if you

01:14:51.174 --> 01:14:53.340
can assume you have a Bloch
vector which oscillates,

01:14:53.340 --> 01:14:55.940
and the Bloch vector
superposition [INAUDIBLE]

01:14:55.940 --> 01:14:58.350
excited state oscillates
at the natural frequency,

01:14:58.350 --> 01:15:00.600
and this Bloch
vector just rotates,

01:15:00.600 --> 01:15:02.855
it doesn't have a hiccup,
it doesn't change its phase

01:15:02.855 --> 01:15:05.860
when the atom collides
with the buffer gas atom.

01:15:05.860 --> 01:15:09.020
So we assume that we have such
a buffer gas where collisions

01:15:09.020 --> 01:15:11.600
don't change the
internal coherence.

01:15:17.480 --> 01:15:23.420
And by internal coherence,
I mean the phase

01:15:23.420 --> 01:15:31.370
between the ground state
and the excited state.

01:15:31.370 --> 01:15:33.700
So in this situation--
but it's actually

01:15:33.700 --> 01:15:36.320
a very important situation
which has been reached,

01:15:36.320 --> 01:15:37.390
in many cases.

01:15:37.390 --> 01:15:41.060
In this situation,
we have-- thus,

01:15:41.060 --> 01:15:48.100
the buffer gas acts only on the
external motion of the atom.

01:15:48.100 --> 01:15:51.950
And now you can
say, in some way,

01:15:51.950 --> 01:15:54.360
the buffer gas acts like a trap.

01:15:54.360 --> 01:15:56.277
The particle wants
to fly away, but it

01:15:56.277 --> 01:15:58.160
collides with the
buffer gas atom.

01:15:58.160 --> 01:16:01.840
And with a certain probability
or after a few collisions,

01:16:01.840 --> 01:16:03.768
it returns back to the origin.

01:16:12.450 --> 01:16:15.475
However, it's a lousy
trap, because there

01:16:15.475 --> 01:16:17.920
is some randomness
and effusive motion.

01:16:17.920 --> 01:16:21.850
So if you want to
describe it as a trap,

01:16:21.850 --> 01:16:25.906
it would be a trap with a wide
spread of trap frequencies.

01:16:41.201 --> 01:16:41.700
OK.

01:16:45.760 --> 01:16:49.710
So if we use this
picture now, what

01:16:49.710 --> 01:16:52.355
we have learned from
ion traps-- remember,

01:16:52.355 --> 01:16:55.220
we had an ion trap
with a sharp carrier.

01:16:55.220 --> 01:17:00.150
And then we had sidebands
at the trap frequency.

01:17:00.150 --> 01:17:04.350
But if we have sort of
now a lousy trap which

01:17:04.350 --> 01:17:06.745
each realization, each
moment has a different trap

01:17:06.745 --> 01:17:08.760
frequency when
waving all my arms,

01:17:08.760 --> 01:17:11.740
I would say for the other
part of the ensemble,

01:17:11.740 --> 01:17:14.620
we get a carrier, and
we have something else.

01:17:14.620 --> 01:17:19.160
And for another realization,
we have another trap frequency.

01:17:19.160 --> 01:17:23.000
So if I use a little bit
of artistic intuition here,

01:17:23.000 --> 01:17:26.310
I would expect, based
on what we learned

01:17:26.310 --> 01:17:32.896
from the previous discussion,
that in such a buffer gas,

01:17:32.896 --> 01:17:37.490
I would have a sharp
carrier, and then I

01:17:37.490 --> 01:17:40.170
would have sort of
a pedestal, which

01:17:40.170 --> 01:17:43.740
is the envelope of
many trap frequencies.

01:17:43.740 --> 01:17:48.440
And we know sort of that the
envelope of all our sticks--

01:17:48.440 --> 01:17:53.150
this was actually given
by the Doppler effect.

01:17:53.150 --> 01:18:00.865
So what we may expect now
is that in this situation

01:18:00.865 --> 01:18:04.330
with buffer gas, we
get a sharp line.

01:18:04.330 --> 01:18:07.260
And then we have
this broad pedestal,

01:18:07.260 --> 01:18:09.860
which you can think
[INAUDIBLE] intuitive picture

01:18:09.860 --> 01:18:12.720
as smeared outside bands.

01:18:12.720 --> 01:18:16.890
And I may call that
the Doppler pedestal.

01:18:16.890 --> 01:18:22.385
And we would expect--
and I discussed that

01:18:22.385 --> 01:18:23.935
with the basal
function, that there

01:18:23.935 --> 01:18:27.330
is one limit where the
envelope of all those sticks

01:18:27.330 --> 01:18:30.855
eventually looks like a
Doppler-broadened line.

01:18:38.780 --> 01:18:40.200
Anyway, time is over.

01:18:40.200 --> 01:18:44.290
But let me just give an outlook.

01:18:44.290 --> 01:18:46.206
On Friday, what
I want to do is I

01:18:46.206 --> 01:18:48.820
want to calculate the width
of this line with you.

01:18:48.820 --> 01:18:52.510
And remember, all
we have to do is

01:18:52.510 --> 01:18:55.450
we have to calculate the
correlation function.

01:18:55.450 --> 01:18:59.510
Previously, when I derived
for you Doppler broadening,

01:18:59.510 --> 01:19:05.620
the correlation function
was the kx becoming kvt.

01:19:05.620 --> 01:19:09.710
kvt, where x became vt
how much the atom moves

01:19:09.710 --> 01:19:11.500
with the velocity v.

01:19:11.500 --> 01:19:15.960
By simply replacing the
linear motion, V times t,

01:19:15.960 --> 01:19:21.150
with a diffusive model, we
can calculate the line shape.

01:19:21.150 --> 01:19:25.670
And we will actually find
that the central line is not

01:19:25.670 --> 01:19:28.550
infinitely sharp,
but it has a width

01:19:28.550 --> 01:19:30.760
which is given by the
diffusion constant.

01:19:30.760 --> 01:19:32.950
And if the diffusion
constant is very, very small,

01:19:32.950 --> 01:19:34.838
we approach a very sharp line.

01:19:37.780 --> 01:19:42.550
And the final comment is, and
this is called Dicke narrowing.

01:19:42.550 --> 01:19:45.120
It is this
counterintuitive result

01:19:45.120 --> 01:19:49.190
that collisions, if they
have those properties,

01:19:49.190 --> 01:19:50.890
are not broadening the line.

01:19:50.890 --> 01:19:54.650
They actually narrow the line
from the [INAUDIBLE] Doppler

01:19:54.650 --> 01:19:56.790
width to something
which is much sharper.

01:19:56.790 --> 01:20:01.590
And this has been useful for
high precision spectroscopy.

01:20:01.590 --> 01:20:04.065
But I think with the concept
which we discussed today

01:20:04.065 --> 01:20:09.910
of confinement, you realize
why collisions can actually

01:20:09.910 --> 01:20:12.940
reduce the line widths,
namely by preventing

01:20:12.940 --> 01:20:17.924
the atoms from acquiring
random phases with respect

01:20:17.924 --> 01:20:20.620
to the drive field [INAUDIBLE].

01:20:20.620 --> 01:20:23.260
Any questions?

01:20:23.260 --> 01:20:25.960
So see you on Friday
in this other building,

01:20:25.960 --> 01:20:27.760
this other lecture
hall that's just

01:20:27.760 --> 01:20:30.210
been announced on the website.